\{x_n\}
x_n=\sum_{k=1}^{n^2}\frac{1}{\sqrt{n^4+k}}
\lim_{n\to \infty }x_n=\lim_{n\to \infty }\sum_{k=1}^{n^2}\frac{1}{\sqrt{n^4+k}}=\lim_{m\to \infty }\frac{1}{m} \sum_{k=1}^{m}\frac{1}{\sqrt{1+\frac{k}{m^2}}}
k=1
k=n^2
1
 \frac{1}{\sqrt{n^4+n^2}} \leq \frac{1}{\sqrt{n^4+k}}\leq \frac{1}{\sqrt{n^4+1}}. 
 \frac{1}{\sqrt{1+1/n^2}}=\frac{n^2}{\sqrt{n^4+n^2}} \leq x_n \leq \frac{n^2}{\sqrt{n^4+1}}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{1+1/n^4}} . 
\lim_{n\rightarrow +\infty} x_n=1
\lim_{x\rightarrow\infty}x_n = 0
\sum \frac{1}{n}
\lim_{L\rightarrow\infty} \int_1^L \frac{1}{\sqrt{L^2+x}} = \lim_{L\rightarrow\infty} 2\left( \sqrt{L^2+L} - \sqrt{L^2+1} \right) = \lim_{L\rightarrow\infty} 2\frac{L-1}{\sqrt{L^2+L} + \sqrt{L^2+1}} = 1
k\le m
1\lt \sqrt{1+\frac{k}{m^2}}\lt 1+\frac{k}{2m^2}.
\frac{1}{\sqrt{1+\frac{k}{m^2}}} \ge \frac{1}{1+\frac{m}{2m^2}}.
\sqrt{n^4+k}\le \sqrt{n^4+n^2}\lt n^2+\frac{1}{2}
